n General Assembly in 2013. All participants will provide signed, written, informed consent stating that participation is voluntary and can be withdrawn at any time. This study was approved by the Institutional Review Board of the Seoul National University Bundang Hospital (B-1605/346-003) and Seoul National University Boramae Medical Center (16-2016-113). The trial protocol has been registered at <ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.clinicaltrials.gov">http://www.clinicaltrials.gov</ext-link> (NCT02887469).</p></sec></ack><ref-list id="Bib1"><title>References</title><ref id="CR1"><label>1.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Spasovski</surname><given-names>G</given-names></name><name><surname>Vanholder</surname><given-names>R</given-names></name><name><surname>Allolio</surname><given-names>B</given-names></name><name><surname>Annane</surname><given-names>D</given-names></name><name><surname>Ball</surname><given-names>S</given-names></name><name><surname>Bichet</surname><given-names>D</given-names></name><etal/></person-group><article-title>Clinical practice guideline on diagnosis and treatment of hyponatraemia</article-title><source>Eur J Endocrinol</source><year>2014</year><volume>170</volume><issue>3</issue><fpage>G1</fpage><lpage>G47</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1530/EJE-13-1020</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">24569125</pub-id></element-citation></ref><ref id="CR2"><label>2.</label><element-citation publication-type="journal"><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Decaux</surname><given-names>G</given-names></name></person-group><article-title>Is asymptomatic hyponatremia really asymptomatic?</article-title><source>Am J Med</source><year>2006</year><volume>119</volume><issue>7 Suppl 1</issue><fpage>S79</fpage><lpage>S82</lpage><pub-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1016/j.amjmed.2006.05.013</pub-id><pub-id pub-id-type="pmid">16843090</pub-id></element-citatio